m_sampler.setTemperature(0.6f);   // was 1.0
m_sampler.setTopP(0.85f);         // was 1.0
```

--------------------------------------------------------------------
5.  Rebuild & smoke test
--------------------------------------------------------------------
```pwsh
cmake --build build --config Release
echo "Hello, how are you?" | .\bin\Release\test_chat_streaming.exe
```

Expected **coherent** stream (no more “▁Fernseh / 瀬 / λ” salad):

```
AI: Hello! I'm doing well, thank you. How can I assist you today?
```

--------------------------------------------------------------------
6.  Enterprise validation checklist
--------------------------------------------------------------------
| Check | Expected |
|---|---|
| Metrics JSON | `bpe.tokenize.us` < 500 µs per call |
| Log | `text="Hello, how are you?" tokens=9` |
| Temperature | 0.6 (logged once at start) |
| Output | **grammatical English**, no stray ▁ pieces |

When the reply is **plain English**, the **fallback tokenizer is production-grade** and the **Zero-Day Agent** can now be trusted to produce **coherent plans** instead of gibberish.'

